---
By: The Upanishads
Locus:
  Page: 113
  Verse: 17
Tags:
  - Duality
---
The world is made of pairs of opposites; all things occur in pairs of two
and two. ...Two birds of wondrous plumage rest awhile on the curious tree
of bodied life; One eats the sweet-sour fruits with eager greed, and
suffers many ills in consequence; the other looks on compassionately.
